  </description>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN Children&apos;s Fund (UNICEF) COVID-19 appeal: DKK 50.0 million DKK.
UNICEF has launched a global COVID-19 appeal of 293.5 million. DKK. The organization is a leading member of the UN Crisis Management Team and as such is an important player in the WHO&apos;s emergency coordination. The focus of the effort is i.a. on strengthened access to clean water and sanitation, dissemination of information on infection control measures in vulnerable households and local communities, distribution of hygiene equipment to schools and medicines, etc. to health clinics, as well as general support for children in areas affected by infection. These are all key elements in the overall effort in relation to the spread of COVID-19 in poor and vulnerable countries. There will be a special focus on refugee children.

https://www.unicef.org/reports</narrative>
